# =============================================================================
# Project Rosetta .gitignore
# =============================================================================
# This file defines what should NOT be tracked in the documentation corpus.
# The corpus itself (corpus/) is tracked; the per-stack workspaces (stack-*/) are not.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STACK WORKSPACES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each stack-*/ directory is a gitignored scratchpad that "spans" one full local
# stack: its cloned platform service repos PLUS its own clone of the
# rosetta-extensions tooling monorepo, checked out at a pinned tag
# (stack-<role>/rosetta-extensions @ <tag>). One directory per stack:
#   stack-dev/    - the local DEV stack (platform repos + its dev tooling clone)
#   stack-demo/   - disposable demo stacks (Clerkenstein-wired, offset ports)
#   stack-dev-2/  - a secondary dev stack
#   stack-stage/, stack-tests/, ...  - future stacks, same pattern
#
# This keeps the documentation corpus clean while allowing hands-on stack work.
# The rosetta-extensions AUTHORING copy (where tooling is built/tested/tagged)
# lives separately under .agentspace/ — see the AGENTSPACE block below.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/stack-*/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ENVIRONMENT & SECRETS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Never commit secrets or environment-specific configuration.
# These may appear if someone accidentally creates them at repo root.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
credentials.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS-SPECIFIC FILES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Linux
*~
.directory

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EDITOR & IDE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VSCode (workspace settings are OK, but user settings are not)
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

# JetBrains IDEs
.idea/

# Vim
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
Session.vim

# Emacs
*~
\#*\#
.#*

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TEMPORARY & GENERATED
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs
*.log
logs/

# Temporary files
tmp/
temp/
*.tmp
*.temp

# Build artifacts (shouldn't exist in a docs repo, but just in case)
dist/
build/
out/

# Node modules (if any tooling is added)
node_modules/

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.Python
*.egg-info/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DOCUMENTATION TOOLING (if added later)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MkDocs / Sphinx / Hugo build output
site/
_build/
public/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CLAUDE CODE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude Code may create local settings that shouldn't be shared
.claude/settings.local.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AGENTSPACE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local scratchpad for skill output: test-platform reports, future skills'
# transient artifacts. The skill writes timestamped markdown reports here;
# they're for the operator to read, not for the corpus.
#
# ALSO hosts the rosetta-extensions AUTHORING copy at .agentspace/rosetta-extensions/
# — the single working clone you spawn on demand to READ / BUILD / TEST the stack
# tooling before committing + tagging it. Each stack then consumes a pinned-tag
# clone under its own stack-*/ dir (see the STACK WORKSPACES block above).
.agentspace/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EMAIL / MARKETING ASSETS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Binary images staged for email campaigns (e.g. Ant Academy launch). These are
# marketing assets, not corpus documentation, and should be kept out of the repo.
_email-assets/
